## Plan Summary

**Root cause:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts` at line 7.

```typescript
// BUG — stops one short of the last element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// FIX — iterates all elements
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the loop condition means a 3-item array only processes indices 0 and 1 (never index 2). A single-item array processes nothing at all.

**Scope of change:** One character removed (`- 1`) in one file — `src/utils.ts` line 7. No test changes needed; the existing 6 tests in `tests/utils.test.ts` already cover all the failing cases and will pass once the fix is applied.

**Verification:** `npx vitest run` — all 6 tests should go green.

